            <h3>About the JWST Multimedia Experience</h3>
            <p>
                Welcome to an immersive journey through the cosmos! This multimedia experience showcases the
                awe-inspiring discoveries made by the <span class="highlight">James Webb Space Telescope (JWST)</span>,
                the most powerful space observatory ever built. Our goal is to convey the essence of JWST's mission
                while igniting curiosity and wonder about the universe we inhabit.
            </p>
            <p>
                Utilizing breathtaking imagery of distant galaxies, star formation, and exoplanets captured by JWST,
                this project blends stunning visuals with an original musical score that evokes feelings of vastness,
                mystery, and excitement. Each piece of music has been carefully selected to enhance the emotional impact
                of the visuals, creating a cohesive and immersive experience.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="big-bang" class="big-bang-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h3>The Big Bang and JWST's Role</h3>
            <p>
                The James Webb Space Telescope is helping to unlock the mysteries of the universe's origins by capturing
                light from the first stars and galaxies that formed after the <span class="highlight">Big Bang</span>.
                Through its powerful infrared vision, JWST is peering deeper into the cosmos than ever before, allowing
                scientists to study the early universe and understand how it evolved into what we see today.
            </p>
            <div class="big-bang-image">
                <img src="/resources/bigBangImg.avif" alt="Big Bang Illustration" height="70%" width="50%">
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="discoveries" class="discoveries-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h3>Notable Discoveries by JWST</h3>
            <ul class="discoveries-list">
                <li>
                    <h4>Galaxy Cluster SMACS 0723</h4>
                    <p>
                        JWST’s deep field image of this galaxy cluster reveals thousands of galaxies, providing insight
                        into
                        the formation and evolution of early structures in the universe.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4>Exoplanet Atmospheres</h4>
                    <p>
                        Using spectroscopy, JWST has detected water and other molecules in the atmospheres of distant
                        exoplanets,
                        advancing our understanding of potentially habitable worlds.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4>Star Formation in the Carina Nebula</h4>
                    <p>
                        The telescope’s stunning imagery of the Carina Nebula reveals newly formed stars and stellar
                        nurseries,
                        shedding light on the process of star formation.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
